Biography

Elizabeth Sanders (Saunders) was born on 21 September 1847 in Tipton, Staffordshire. She was the daughter of Charlotte Saunders.[1]

In the 1851 census Elizabeth Dace (age 3) was the daughter of John Dace on Guns Lane, West Bromwich, Staffordshire, England.[2]

In the 1861 census Elizabeth Dace (age 13) was the daughter of John Dace on Piercy St, West Bromwich, Staffordshire, England.[3]

Elizabeth was baptised on 19 August 1866 in Saint Thomas, Dudley, Worcester, England.[4]

When Elizabeth was 20 she married in October 1866 in Dudley, Staffordshire.[5]

In the 1871 census Elizth Timbs (age 24) was the wife of John Timbs in Tipton, Staffordshire, England.[6]

Elizabeth died at the age of 79 between September and December 1925 in Salford, Lancashire, England.[10][11]

Research Notes

Date of birth on baptism record in 1866, prior to her marriage was 21 September 1846. However, this is probably incorrect, as it seems more likely that her birth was registered in the March Quarter of 1846 under the name Sanders.

This does not fit with her age in 1851 and 1861 censuses and the birth of an Elizabeth Saunders in the Dudley registration district in September quarter is more likely since Tipton is in this district and the year should have been 1847. The citation has been changed.Buckle-52 10:22, 1 February 2024 (UTC)

Elizabeth Saunders Dace (age 20), daughter of John Dace, a Farrier, married John Timbs (age 40) on 7 October 1866 in Tipton, St Martin, Staffordshire, England.[12][13]
